  <mainContent><![CDATA[<h3>An apprenticeship is a nationally recognised qualification, giving you the change to combine hands-on training with academic study.</h3>
<p>(As an apprentice you will typically be in the workplace four days a week learning relevant skills and knowledge from your colleagues. On the other day, you will be in college exploring your desired industry with trained specialists.</p>
<p>You will learn all of this whilst earning a minimum wage of £3.70 an hour, but many employers pay more than this.</p>
<h3>Benefits of studying an Apprenticeships</h3>
<ul>
<li>Earn a salary and receive paid holiday</li>
<li>Learning tailored towards your individual needs</li>
<li>Access to industry standard facilities and resources</li>
<li>Teacher’s and Assessors with real-life industry experience</li>
<li>Excellent progression opportunities</li>
</ul>]]></mainContent>
